divs: sighting detailsi started work at about 5:45 am at an ambulance company where i'm a driver\emt-b with the state. my partner and i headed east on route 92 and saw a "fish" in the sky. my partner has a camera phone and we stopped to take a pic of it at about 6:00am. we both thought it was a cloud breaking up and sunlight coming from behind. we ran an emergency response call that we were later relased from that found us traveling east on hwy 60, brandon blvd, in brandon, fla. the clock reads 6:10 when we pull into a gas station for some morning coffiee. outside the truck we notice this is no cloud but a condensation trail for the sky was completly clear of any clouds. standing for a total of 5 minutes we watch another streak of trail materialize before our eyes. people are now stopping and asking us what it is and what is causing it. i observe others taking pics as my partner continues to shoot from her phone. it is now approx 6:30am and the condensation trails continue to grow larger and with more color, like green, blue, bright white. another car arrives and a man stops to ask us what it is. he goes to one of the gas pumps and we don't see him again for about 15 more minutes. we go back to our truck to get a better position since the sun has now broke the horizon. upon doing so, the man in the car returns and faces us both in the eastern position. he states he has been watching these two objects in the ":" postion at about the 10 o'clock spot. he directs us to a ring of condensation where i too and my partner spot the objects of either metallic material or very bright light. we observe them staying still but floating like in a liquid. the lower object travels in a south east direction at a quick pace and vanishes. the top object stays in place for about 60 seconds and travels in an up, north east direction and also vanishes. i have, nor has my ambulance partner, ever seen such a sight. the man from the car states the same information. i know nasa launched a rocket at approx 5:30am that morning going to mars.
